<synopsis><code mime="text/x-python">
@accepts(gdouble, gdouble)
@returns(none)
def set_scale(scale_x, scale_y)
</code></synopsis>
<p>Scales an actor with the given factors. The scaling is relative to
the scale center and the anchor point. The scale center is
unchanged by this function and defaults to 0,0.</p><p>The <link xref="Clutter.Actor-scale-x">Clutter.Actor:scale-x</link> and <link xref="Clutter.Actor-scale-y">Clutter.Actor:scale-y</link> properties are
animatable.</p>

